00035     *((std::string*)fInputMapIter->second.varAddress) = *inputString;
00036     return true;

00039     std::vector<std::string>* stringVec =

00104 bool ORVOrcaRequestProcessor::LoadInput(const std::string& varName, 
00105   const ORDictValueA* dictArray) 
00106 {
00107   fInputMapIter = fInputMap.find(varName);
00108   if(fInputMapIter == fInputMap.end()) {
00109     ORLog(kError) << varName << " is not a registered input of: " 
00110       << GetNameOfRequestProcessor() << endl;
00111     return false;
00112   }
00113   if(fInputMapIter->second.type != kRealVec 
00114      && fInputMapIter->second.type != kIntVec 
00115      && fInputMapIter->second.type != kStringVec) {
00116     ORLog(kError) << "Invalid type for: " << varName << " in "
00117       << GetNameOfRequestProcessor() << endl;
00118     return false;
00119   }
00120   if(dictArray->GetNValues()==0) return true;
00121   /* Not loading anything*/
00122 
00123   ORVDictValue::EValType type = dictArray->At(0)->GetValueType();
00124   switch(type) {
00125     case ORVDictValue::kString: {
00126         if(fInputMapIter->second.type != kStringVec) {
00127           ORLog(kError) << "String type needed for array " 
00128           << varName << endl;
00129           return false;
00130         }
00131         std::vector<std::string>* stringVec = 
00132           ((std::vector<std::string>*)fInputMapIter->second.varAddress);
00133         stringVec->resize(dictArray->GetNValues());
00134         for(size_t i=0;i<dictArray->GetNValues();i++) {
00135           (*stringVec)[i] = 
00136             dynamic_cast<const ORDictValueS*>(dictArray->At(i))->GetS();
00137         }
00138       }
00139       break;
00140     case ORVDictValue::kInt: {
00141         if(fInputMapIter->second.type != kIntVec) {
00142           ORLog(kError) << "Int type needed for array " 
00143           << varName << endl;
00144           return false;
00145         }
00146         std::vector<int>* intVec = 
00147           ((std::vector<int>*)fInputMapIter->second.varAddress);
00148         intVec->resize(dictArray->GetNValues());
00149         for(size_t i=0;i<dictArray->GetNValues();i++) {
00150           (*intVec)[i] = 
00151             dynamic_cast<const ORDictValueI*>(dictArray->At(i))->GetI();
00152         }
00153       }
00154       break;
00155     case ORVDictValue::kReal: {
00156         if(fInputMapIter->second.type != kRealVec) {
00157           ORLog(kError) << "Real type needed for array " 
00158           << varName << endl;
00159           return false;
00160         }
00161         std::vector<double>* doubleVec = 
00162           ((std::vector<double>*)fInputMapIter->second.varAddress);
00163         doubleVec->resize(dictArray->GetNValues());
00164         for(size_t i=0;i<dictArray->GetNValues();i++) {
00165           (*doubleVec)[i] = 
00166             dynamic_cast<const ORDictValueR*>(dictArray->At(i))->GetR();
00167         }
00168       }
00169       break;
00170     default: {
00171         ORLog(kDebug) << "Unknown type: " << type << endl;
00172         return false;
00173       }
00174       break;
00175   }
00176    
00177   return true;
00178     
00179 }
